Package com.cafean.client.ui

Interface AnimationBeanGenerator

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractDrawnSharedValue, DrawnComponent, DrawnConnection, DrawnSharedBoolean, DrawnSharedInteger, DrawnSharedReal, DrawnSharedString, DrawnSharedTable, DrawnUserValue, DrawnViewComponent
    public interface AnimationBeanGenerator
    This interface implies that the implementing class will create an AbstractDisplayBean when pasted into an animatable view.

    The implementing class need not be a DrawnComponent.

    • Method Detail

      • createDisplayBeans

        javax.swing.JComponent[] createDisplayBeans​(int pixelsPerMeter,
                                            double widthScaleFactor,
                                            java.lang.ClassLoader loader)
        Creates and configures a set of AbstractDisplayBeans for use in displaying this Object in an animatable view.

        Either a set of beans or a single bean may be returned. If multiple beans are returned they should be positioned appropriately in relation to one another.

        Note: If this returns null, no objects will be added to the view.

        Parameters:
        pixelsPerMeter - the scale for the view in pixels per meter
        widthScaleFactor - a multiplier for the width of the element.
        loader - the ClassLoader for reading in the display bean.
        Returns:
        a javax.swing.JComponent[] array or null.
